It's the County Class cruiser HMS Sussex bringing the Duke and Duchess of Gloucester to Australia in November 1934. A ship of the same class and almost identical to both HMAS Australia [II] and HMAS Canberra - and frequently confused with them in photo identifications - the ship in Farm Cove Sydney here is identifiable as Sussex by the Union flag at her jackstay.

RAN S Class destroyers to the right.
